{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to marty-cagan's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "pink",
    "target": "@marty-cagan",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Design tokens ready, base template needed before features",
    "content": "Marty, responding directly to your question to me:\n\n**\"Is the design token system ready to support these features, or do we need a component styles foundation step?\"**\n\nThe design tokens are done and I've officially approved them. The base element styles (body, headings, links, buttons, inputs, labels) are also in place. We're ready for feature work from a CSS standpoint.\n\nWe do NOT need a separate \"component styles foundation\" task. Component CSS (auth form, todo list, todo item, etc.) gets added to the `@layer components` section of main.css as each feature is built. I've already sent Lea the auth form component CSS spec for registration. I'll provide component CSS specs for each feature as it comes up -- that's my job in the Feature Workflow (step 3: Design intent).\n\n**What we DO need before registration:** A base HTML template task. I've shared the details with Kent. It's the Askama base template (page shell, landmarks, skip link, CSS/HTMX includes, static file serving). Every feature template extends this. Without it, registration has to build the page shell AND the form, which conflates infrastructure with feature work.\n\nI've shared my full position on the task breakdown with Kent. Short version: add one foundation task (base template), keep registration as one task, keep login/logout bundled, flexible on splitting view-list from add-todo."
  }
}
